{
  "local_port": 59950,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the books to improve English?",
  "response": "Improving your English can be achieved through a variety of books that cater to different aspects of the language, including vocabulary, grammar, writing, and reading comprehension. Here are some popular and effective books you can consider:\n\n1. **Grammar**:\n   - *English Grammar in Use* by Raymond Murphy: A comprehensive book that covers all the grammar you need in practice exercises.\n   - *The Elements of Style* by William Strunk Jr. and E.B. White: A classic for understanding the principles of English style and composition.\n\n2. **Vocabulary**:\n   - *Word Power Made Easy* by Norman Lewis: A helpful book for building and enhancing your vocabulary skills through etymology.\n\n3. **Writing**:\n   - *On Writing: A Memoir of the Craft* by Stephen King: Offers advice and tips on the craft of writing from one of the most successful authors.\n   - *The Writing Life* by Annie Dillard: Insights into the writing process and the life of a writer.\n\n4. **Reading Comprehension**:\n   - *Reading Comprehension Success in 20 Minutes a Day* by LearningExpress: Improves your reading skills through short, structured lessons.\n\n5. **Pronunciation and Accent**:\n   - *Clear Speech* by Judy B. Gilbert: Focuses on improving English pronunciation and listening skills with audio.\n\n6. **General Skills**:\n   - *The Oxford English Dictionary*: Comprehensive resource for building a strong vocabulary and understanding usage.\n   - *Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary*: Another authoritative resource for English definitions and grammar usage.\n   \n7. **Advanced and Style Insights**:\n   - *Style: Toward Clarity and Grace* by Joseph M. Williams: Offers guidance on creating clear and engaging writing.\n\n8. **For ESL Learners**:\n   - *ESL Intermediate/Advanced Grammar* by Mary Ellen Munoz Page: Provides grammar rules and practice exercises for ESL learners aiming to improve their proficiency.\n   - *The Blue Book of Grammar and Punctuation* by Jane Straus: Offers easy-to-understand rules and guidelines on grammar and punctuation.\n\nAdditionally, reading a wide range of English literature \u2014 from classic novels to modern works \u2014 can also greatly improve your language skills. Engaging regularly with the language in varied contexts can enhance your comprehension and fluency.",
